25/09/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The NATO HQ Commander in Macedonia, Brigadier General John Durance, said in an interview with Radio Free Europe that the country's reform programme is proceeding well but that more work is needed in certain fields, such as judicial reforms and fighting corruption.
In the interview Sunday (24 September), Durance noted that Macedonia has made significant progress as regards defence sector restructuring.
He reiterated that NATO's doors remain open to new members.
(Vecer - 25/09/06;
Makfax, A1 TV - 24/09/06)
